title: Suspect in LaPlace teen's murder arrested in Houston, website reports
content:
A 22-year-old man wanted in the shooting death of a LaPlace teenager was arrested in Houston, L'Observateur reports.
Frederick Seymore is suspected of shooting 16-year-old Tory Horton, a rising sophomore at East St. John High School. Authorities discovered Seymore's Toyota Corolla on Wednesday in Jefferson Parish, the report said.
A second man, Bruce Butler, was also arrested in connection with the murder.
